<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-02T21:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-02T21:40:00-05:00" n="449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/979.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-02T22:00:00-04:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1913—10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Inflammatory speeches by opposition tonight precipitated conflict between
                            Government guards and the mob, causing several deaths and many wounded;
                            there were numerous arrests. Both sides are deaf to <pb facs="0543" n="439" xml:id="pg_439"/> reason and the time has arrived for
                            positive action. The Government seems determined to employ the old
                            coercive measures and is intolerant of criticism. I recommend that it be
                            warned that the Department will shut off revenues if force should be
                            used to carry the election.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>